    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A noncontact, light microscopy imaging system allowing for three-dimensional surface analysis. The objective lens has its image distance set to infinity. This depth of field is combined with vertical scanning to traverse the surface of a sample providing a high resolution topographical image with a large field of view. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
